##Sealing off the city of Huanggang: In the affected area, the sons'medicine was delivered

Function introduction, record the rise and fall of the characters and changes in the value of the Times. Complete, true, in-depth, accurate non-fiction stories, sent to you every week.

When can Hubei people go back to Beijing? Is still unknown. The hometown of young writer Deng Anqing is Huanggang Wuxue, 200 kilometers away from Wuhan. Every Spring Festival, he and tens of millions of people like to go home for a week to stay in the New Year and then back to work. On January 23, the city of Wuhan was closed, and the next day, the city of Huanggang and its counties and cities were closed. Until now, the situation has been grim.
More than once during the plague, he found that his father's "resignation" had been replaced by a new way of communicating with his neighbors. Meanwhile, the village funeral was also hastily arranged, "If the oxygen tanks had been removed years ago and people buried, it wouldn't be so awkward now, " he said, wondering what my parents would have done if I had left home alone?

When can Hubei people go back to Beijing? Is still unknown. The hometown of young writer Deng Anqing is Huanggang Wuxue, 200 kilometers away from Wuhan. Every Spring Festival, he and tens of millions of people like to go home for a week to stay in the New Year and then back to work. On January 23, the city of Wuhan was closed, and the next day, the city of Huanggang and its counties and cities were closed. Until now, the situation has been grim.

More than once during the plague, he found that his father's "resignation" had been replaced by a new way of communicating with his neighbors. Meanwhile, the village funeral was also hastily arranged, "If the oxygen tanks had been removed years ago and people buried, it wouldn't be so awkward now, " he said, wondering what my parents would have done if I had left home alone?

···············

❶

From the infected areas

My father ran out of insulin again, and my brother, who lived downtown, agreed. He bought the medicine and sent it to the 100 meter port gate. My mother and I drove the three-wheeler to pick him up. When we got to the gate, the earthen barricade blocked the road, so we had to stop the car and step over it.

Between the two mounds was a bridge, and we met in the middle of it. I took my mother's bag of fresh vegetables, potato flour, Sauerkraut, and my nephew's crayons to my brother's electric car, and he handed me the medicine.

It was the first time we had seen each other since January 31, when motor vehicles were banned. It was the middle of February. Although in the same city, they live in downtown Wuxue, we are in the countryside, a straight line distance of about ten kilometers. If you drive, you'll be home in less than 20 minutes. If father's medicine hadn't run out, I'm afraid we wouldn't have had a chance to see each other.

My brother bought my father a protamine-based synthetic human insulin injection. My father, who had diabetes, was given the drug every day. If the drug for a period of time, will cause high blood sugar, causing nausea, vomiting, lethargy, loss of appetite and other symptoms. The consequences are too great to be taken lightly.

Last week, the medicine also ran out, the city could not go, we had to bike to the town to buy medicine, to the Bayi Gate, the road is also set up roadblocks, cars can not drive through. My father asked me to stay and watch the car. He went into town to buy medicine. I said I'll go. He won't let me. I don't know about the pills.

When he came back, I could see from a distance his slow, limp pace, his lungs choking on the hill, his feet in the mud, his legs hunched. I hurried over to help him, his clothes are wet under the armpits. When I asked him how he was doing, he shook his head. "All the pharmacies are closed. No one answers the phone. No one on the street. "

Fortunately, I managed to get someone to buy the insulin, otherwise I would have been in trouble. But I'll never forget the way he walked, the pain never went away.

This time, luckily, my brother managed to get it from a pharmacy downtown. If we go to the back and take further measures to seal off the area, and the pharmacy is not open, where can we buy it? If we have to go to the hospital, is it safe to go there now? After all, according to the official release of information, confirmed infection cases of more than 200 points... these are practical difficulties to be encountered in the future, to think about the headache.

❷

If I leave home alone,

What about my parents?

We should go back when my brother is gone. I sat in the back of my car as my mother drove home on the three-wheeler. I wanted to drive. Mother was worried. In her eyes, I will always be that reckless child. The Yangtze River Levee used to be a major traffic artery, but now you can walk safely without a car in front or behind you. Open Open, my mother stopped, asked me cold, when the river breeze blowing, I said not cold. Mother drove on, much slower. I know. She's still afraid I'm cold.

I remembered that my father had driven me to town in the same car the week before. On the drive, my father said something. The wind was so strong that I couldn't hear it clearly. Asked again, he said: "I'm afraid you won't be back to Beijing for a while. " I loudly replied: "Yes, our company said to start late. " Father smiled. When I asked him why he was laughing, he said, "this is the first time in years that you've stayed at home for this long. "

Father fell asleep watching TV.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I have been at home for almost a month since I left Beijing on January 19. I asked myself if I regretted coming back, after all, I knew there was an epidemic before I came back. Like many of my friends, I could have canceled my trip and stayed in Beijing, before the outbreak became widespread and safe. Even if back, there are many people took advantage of the "closed city" in the first few hours of the night left Hubei, one of my friends is such, before he specifically asked me to leave together, I refused.

I can't leave without you. What will my parents do if I'm not at home? You know, the first thing I did when I got home was to tell them about the epidemic, and they didn't take it seriously at all, I said as they nodded, and went off to do something.

In any case, what they saw was a quiet and peaceful village, where people had come back from all over the country to get ready for the New Year and to get busy with the new year. What does this affair in Wuhan have to do with us? They can't see the danger. And look at my aunts and uncles. They're just like my parents. If I wasn't there, my parents were stuck at home, not knowing what was going on, not knowing how to protect myself, I wouldn't be able to eat or sleep.

I feel so bad for them. For the past year, I have been a guest at home, staying for a few days and leaving without a suitcase to put in the closet. And mother every day to think of ways to make delicious food for me, for fear that in this short period of time, I did not eat well. Father was ill, I did not accompany him to the hospital, is the mother to take care of him, take medicine is also his father to the pharmacy and hospital. If I'm not there and my brother's not back, what about my father? I can't imagine what it's like to be alone.

I send them money now and then to make up for my lack of company. But they won't use it. I know. They'll save it, and they'll leave it to me. No matter how much I stressed that I would make money, they were unmoved. They always tell me the house is fine. You don't have to worry. I wasn't home, and they just chose to tell me the good things, and they took the bad things on themselves. But not this time. They do not yet know the full extent of the outbreak. So, I had to be home, like the head of the prison watching two prisoners.

❸

"It's the best thing that's ever happened

The loneliest Spring Festival ever."

Back in the day, we watched the epidemic spread to several provinces. As soon as I saw the news, I ran to my parents and told them. The mother side Burns a fire to side a bit fidgety ground to say: "Good Luo well, you why a day arrive black all say this! " I say: "CAN NOT SAY! "! Don't go where there are too many people. Wear a mask! Wash your hands frequently..."mother said:"In the countryside if you wear a mask, do not laugh dead people. "which one do you think is wearing a mask? " I said anxiously. "You can't be careless. Just because someone else doesn't wear it doesn't mean you don't wear it."

After all, I have too many relatives who live and work in Wuhan. They have to come back for the New Year and go from house to house to pay New Year calls. WHO WEARS A mask? Wash your hands often? Everyone is still in the same routine year after year. I can't believe this. But mother still didn't take it to heart.

In order to make my mother have some awareness, I can also be described as "well-intentioned. ". When she came to my room to talk, I showed her a dozen videos of the outbreak. "Is it that serious? " I said. "Of course. You don't see it in the countryside. It's very tense out there. "

We're back to New Year's. What I have a headache is the new year greetings from the first to the third day of the Lunar New Year. I said to my mother, "I wish those relatives wouldn't come to pay their respects. ". A lot of people said they wish they had called to say good-bye. " My mother said, "well, you can't say that. Many relatives don't even have contact information, and they only come once in the new year. " I added, "then you should wear a mask. " My mother said, "it's not polite to wear a mask to greet guests. " I was worried, "is face important, or life important AH? " The mother said: "You do not pay New Year, can not stop others pay New Year. This block can not stop. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Mother's in the kitchen.

And on my father's side, I did the same. He is a very fond of playing cards, whether it is sunny or rainy, he can not stay at home. There is a Mahjong Parlor in the dike. He often goes there to see the cards. When he came back, I gave him the mask, seriously tell him: "GRANDPA, if you run around like this, if you get infected, the whole family will get infected. This is no joke. " My father looked at me in surprise and said: "It's not that serious, don't scare your own family. " I don't care, still slip the mask over his face and make sure he puts it on whenever he goes out. He held the mask over his head. "If I wear this, people will laugh at me, " I said. "I don't care! I can't control people, but you have to wear it. I have to control this. "

However, my father soon stopped going to the Mahjong Parlor. According to him, someone reported that Mahjong Parlors had gathered a crowd to gamble, the police station came, smashed Mahjong tables, but also those who play cards to impose a fine. If we play cards again, we'll have to detain them. All of a sudden, no one's playing cards. My father had to stay home and watch TV. I'm relieved, too.

But what gave me a real sense of relief was what happened on January 25, the first day of the Lunar New Year.

Two days earlier, on January 23, the city of Wuhan was "sealed off" , followed by the city of Huanggang on January 24, the eve of the New Year, and by the afternoon in my hometown of Wuxue.

I told my mother all the news. On the afternoon of the 24th, my mother said to me, "I have already told your brother that I will go to his house in the evening and tomorrow. If a New Year's visitor comes, there will be no one in our family. If anyone asks, he's been out on the street. It seems that nagging about the epidemic every day in front of us has worked. A stone has fallen from my heart.

We spent the New Year's Eve at my brother's home in the city. On the afternoon of the New Year's Day, my brother drove us back to the countryside, out of the community, to the road under the Yangtze River Levee. This road is the main thoroughfare in downtown Wuxue. On the first day of the Lunar New Year, it would have been jammed with people and cars. Soon came to our embankment, every door locked, no one on the concrete road. It seems our fears were misplaced. All of a sudden, we all have a consensus, no one went out new year, are at home, do not drop in.

My mother said, "This is the loneliest Spring Festival I've ever had in my life. " She added, "well, I'm a lot more relaxed. In the past, New Year's greetings came in waves and waves, receiving this and that, too busy. Now I can lie at home. Originally everyone is not willing to go out to pay New Year call, also small Yazi son is happy. Well, now everyone can breathe a sigh of relief."

While talking, the mobile phone rang, a look is a relative call. Then several relatives called. At my mother's urging, I also called a few calls to my uncle, aunt, aunt, they. Everyone said, "just say New Year on the phone. " Happy New Year. Understand. Understand. These are the two sentences we say most during the New Year.

❹

"Don't come any closer. Stay away from me! "

Overnight, everyone's habits changed. The most direct manifestation of this change is distance.

Our dike is a big dike, the overwhelming majority of people are surnamed Deng, in front of the House and behind the house, with relatives, basically are home. Spring Festival is such a rare leisure time, we like to get together to play cards and play Mahjong, when it rains, this family sit and chat, when the weather is fine, sit together in the sun on the court.

But this year, almost none of that happened. From the beginning of the Lunar New Year, I often saw the three-wheeler pass the house, the car has a high-powered amplifier, is playing the radio, as far as possible to stay at home, do not go anywhere; mother said to go to the village to buy vegetables, in addition to a van parked in front of the embankment to prevent vehicles from going in and out, there are special guards, as long as people gather to chat, that person will go to dissuade, and shops are closed; In front of every home were posted the COVID-19 for pneumonia and a letter from the People's Government of Wuxue City to all citizens'friends. Village cadres went door to door distributing disposable face masks, the returnees were also registered and had their temperature taken.

People are basically holed up in their homes, and sometimes it gets really boring, like my dad couldn't help but come out and start wearing masks. You meet people on the road, you don't get together. Want to talk. There's plenty of room between us. The content of everyone's chat also revolved around the epidemic situation. On TV today, it was said how many new confirmed infected people were added to the acupoint of Wu, and which provinces'medical rescue teams came to us, the rice eye of the supermarket looked to raise the price... everyone although chatting, but all set in their own position, not close to each other. If someone does not understand this tacit understanding, walk toward oneself, some people half jest half seriously shout: "You mo come over, leave me alone! "

This change in interpersonal communication was entirely new to my parents and to the previous generation. My generation is used to a certain distance of communication, for my parents, as well as neighbors, need to learn from scratch.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Fresh vegetables picked daily from the garden.

Sometimes I would stand by and listen to them talk. For them, I can no longer well, everyone these decades of fortune in my heart billow. In my books, some of them I've written, some I haven't, some I've merged into one character, some I've splintered into others. The cumulative power of time is in their foreheads, in their hair, in their wrinkles, in the palms of blackish hands, in their hobbling steps, in the tones of their voices.

Apart from the renovation of the houses, the basic pattern of the village has not changed much for decades. The generation I know is fading away, and the new generation is drifting away with its young parents. But this year has provided an opportunity: the younger generation, like me, who only stayed a few days, had to stay. With generations in the same room for so long, the emotions that were too rushed to nurture in the past begin to unfold during this "long vacation. ".

A generation ago, they thought it was a distant thing, but then everyone put on a mask and started to keep their distance. This process of transformation, in addition to the constant propaganda of the government, I think there is also the role of the younger generation. They, like me, kept whispering in their parents'ears to be on the lookout. It's amazing how quickly you can change your way of doing things.

I was also amazed at how much my mother had changed. At home, self-isolation for a long time, sometimes really feel bored, I told my mother I go out for a walk. Mother reminded me to say: "Remember to wear a mask! " I said I know. I had no idea that my mother, who had been so cavalier about wearing a mask, was now supervising me.

❺

Father's "resignation"

Mother took it a step further and supervised my father.

After getting the medicine, I went home and found no trace of my father. Mother angrily said: "I do not know where to go! Do Not die is Bo? ! " Until the evening finally wait for my father back, in the kitchen I told him that the medicine has been got, the Father Happily said: "want to get. "

When he had his injection and returned to the kitchen for dinner, his mother said gravely, "it doesn't matter if your family doesn't want to die. Your whole family still has to live. You must have a sense of proportion! "

Father said: "No matter, I wear a mask! And no one around the infection, do not panic. "

Mother said: "things come late, you did not hear Qinger said, someone out to buy food, just a few minutes time infected, you said nothing! "

The father put his hand out and said, "what can I do? This is fate. "

I once again saw the kind of father's "fate" : he felt in the face of such a disaster, you infected with bad luck, no infection that do not scare themselves. It's fate, anyway. If it comes down to you, there's no point in you running. As for the admonition to wear a mask and wash your hands frequently, it seems to him that it is both troublesome and useless, and that he can not do the tedious work of prevention.

After dinner and watching the news in his room, my father sighed after hearing from the news anchor how many cases were confirmed, suspected, and dead, "people busy a lifetime, suddenly because of this thing died, think really no taste! " Mother Pie mouth way: "You eat it is a taste. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"At home, I found Bohumil Hrabal, tears would come to my eyes. When the epidemic is over in the future, I must go to the Czech Republic to see his tavern and his old house. "

Speaking of death, my parents talked about Fang Ye, who had just died a few days before. A few months ago, Fang Ye was hospitalized because of a sudden cerebral infarction. After he was discharged from the hospital, he had been lying at home. His father went to see him. He had been unconscious for a long time. Fang was about the same age as his parents. His wife, Bai Yunniang, died of liver cancer a few years ago. The sons all set up shop in Jiangsu. Now a son at home guard, other children also can not come back, after all, the temple has been closed.

"If we had removed the oxygen tanks years ago and buried people, it wouldn't be so embarrassing now, " she said

When I asked where the embarrassment lay, my father answered, "If there were no one left, would anyone be there to carry his coffin? The epidemic is so severe that no one would dare cross it. "

I ask again: "Don't cremate now? "

Father replied: "These years is not forced cremation, so now are buried. "

Mother said: "Another, children outside, also can not come back. "

I thought for a moment and said, "now that there is no one left, we have to ask the crematorium people to come and take the body away for cremation. His son will take the ashes back and put them away until the epidemic is over. "

Mother nodded and said, "that's it. It was cremated, brought back in an urn, and quietly buried next to your coffin. Only a few of them went to the house, and the scene was very quiet. "

My father said of Bai Yunniang again, "ooh, how beautiful the funeral was! How presentable! Eight Taoist priests were invited to recite sutras, money was scattered along the road, and various wreaths dazzled my eyes. It cost eighty thousand... "

Mother interrupted: "You are not a few envy? It is a waste of money, people are dead, the money is given to others, have a child flavor? That is to say ostentation speak beautiful. "

My father was scorned beyond words, suddenly he turned to me and said, "If I die, Qinger, I only have one wish. Your brother is holding my urn, you are holding my portrait in the back, your mother is carrying a spade, find a place to bury me casually... "

My mother chuckled and interrupted, "it's so hard! I won't carry a shovel. I'll just take your ashes and throw them into the Yangtze River. "

❻

You are the most important, the most important in the world,

Do you want a kiss?"

In fact, my father had spoken of death more than once.

A few years ago, when I was leaving home, he suddenly asked me if I would like to see the portrait he had already asked someone to draw for him. Years passed, and he brought up the funeral again. We laughed it off, but it stuck in my mind. Yes, it's time I thought about that.

The death toll on the TV right now is making him feel very scared and very nervous. I can feel that. Father got up to go to the toilet, I see him now walk a Rub Rub, face-shaped thin, hunchback, the most important thing is no spirit. My mother whispered to me, "he can't even play cards, he can't even hold them. Once I was told he got up from the table with yellow pants on the back... "

I immediately looked up the Internet, the original complications of diabetes, that is, autonomic nerve damage, incontinence appeared. A little decay of the body necessarily leads to a little decay of the mind. Death, like a heavy blow, is ready to strike. It does not strike, but it strikes.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Mother is blowing the breeze at the door.

One after another, reports of the outbreak continued to be broadcast on television. We watched in silence for a long time. Mother suddenly asked: "Qinger, if I infected with this disease, you will take care of me? " I froze for a moment, then said: "will surely! "

I remembered telling my mother about a young man in Wuhan who was in a critical condition after being infected. His sister nursed him in the ward for several days until he finally recovered from his illness and was discharged. If I can do what his sister did, I don't know. A lot of things will happen, will see their own is brave or cowardly.

My mother nodded and smiled. "I'm an idiot, too, and if I get it, my whole family will probably get it. THAT'S THE PROBLEM! So stay in the house. Being alive is more important than being alive! "

"What son is important? " A turn head, the father went to the toilet to come back.

Mother Pie Pie Mouth said: "You are the most important, the world's most important, to get Bo? "
